RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 11000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PARABELLUM moved clear under mild coaxing, shifted in early on the first turn, set the pace racing on or just off the rail, shook off foes in upper stretch and held sway while being kept to the task. RUNQUIETLY switched outside the leader and eventual winner early on the first turn, stalked that one then edged closer to press up the backstretch racing two to three wide, lost ground into upper stretch but closed the gap late but was only second best. BIG NORTHERN RIVER stalked three to four wide, encouraged along at the quarter pole but ran on evenly. GOLDBRIDGE shifted in on the first turn, tracked inside near the rail, asked for more past the quarter, had no response. GREAT REALIZATION was a bit rank in the early going racing off the inside, saved ground on the far turn before swinging out for the drive but failed to rally.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: KICK IT AGAIN BOB was quickly clear to set the pace racing off the rail, was prompted by an inside rival coming to the half, dueled with that one then began to edge clear again midway on the turn, was clear into mid-stretch, was shortening stride and kept on desperately to just last over. HOLCOMBE was bumped at the break, ranged up outside rivals mid-pack going four to five wide on the turn, was closing willingly but too late. OKIE CHROME tracked from inside the second flight on or just off the rail, needed more. PONZA raced at the back off the rail but inside a foe, went in the three path mostly through the turn, failed to menace. STOLEN GHOST bumped the outside rival at the start, raced at the back outside going four to five wide on the turn, failed to rally. WARRIOR'S STAR shifted in, chased from between runners three wide in the second flight, faded. DUE TO TECHNOLOGICAL MALFUNCTION, FINISH MARGINS PROVIDED BY CHARTCALLER. DUE TO MUTUELS MALFUNCTION ALL WAGERS FOR THIS RACE WERE REFUNDED.
